<taxonomicName id="6A1B129FDBE508E7652675998E11863B" authority="(Sendtn.) Bitter, Abh. Naturwiss. Verein Bremen 24 [preprint]: 499. 1919" authorityName="(Sendtn.) Bitter, Abh. Naturwiss. Verein Bremen 24 [preprint]: 499." authorityYear="1919" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lycianthes synanthera" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="synanthera">Lycianthes synanthera (Sendtn.) Bitter, Abh. Naturwiss. Verein Bremen 24 [preprint]: 499. 1919</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F492604F6C5FCF8FB78FB0B8E3B1E564" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="3D0868DCD5525ABE08EDE44BC6011D03" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="D429A7FA5C8E6A457FE178A9DDC03C48" authorityName="Sendtn" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum synantherum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="synantherum">Solanum synantherum</taxonomicName>
Sendtn., Flora 29 (13): 194 [as 178]. 1846. Type: Guatemala [Costa Rica. Province Alajuela], Monte Aguacate, 
<emphasis id="0AA0FA0FD7C1123894C113B2015AA269" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. von Friedrichsthal 1292</emphasis>
(lectotype designated here: W [acc. # 0003083]; isolectotypes: W [acc. # 0003081, acc. # 0003082], F [F0073153F, acc. # 871594]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="32F3928D478224C229DD9FEA9B0B98A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="56B3783F9B842EFAC3F659D96DC4E59B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8FFD7D2C96B732C0D1DA451E865CEEA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Based on 
<taxonomicName id="ACE460F909C069DFBD908E9AB3E2B946" authorityName="Sendtn" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum synantherum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="synantherum">
<emphasis id="B6ED373AD655A35E252E46A1F0A5EA13" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum synantherum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sendtn.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="47F2D2EB99D34DFE55AD878FBE2011C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
We have not been able to confirm the existence of the usually epiphytic shrub/vine 
<taxonomicName id="B4FFCC8A1287DFF99CFED0F16F0D88FC" genus="L." lsidName="L. synanthera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="synanthera">
<emphasis id="7C04E264C40B776EAF1A18C2883185F6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. synanthera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Guatemala, and it likely does not occur there; we have located and examined many specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="AC03600F30749248A0CCEE6D0495E838" genus="L." lsidName="L. synanthera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="synanthera">
<emphasis id="F1AD9B94063ABA6D60BEA4F305AD99CA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. synanthera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Nicaragua, Costa Rica, and Panama. The type material of 
<taxonomicName id="F384B228CF75D8A940C41E7FB120B44C" authorityName="Sendtn" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum synantherum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="synantherum">
<emphasis id="5F2D2C7C3A672BE9BB1B18EF5B964C1F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum synantherum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected by Friedrichsthal at Monte Aguacate. His labels were preprinted with the word 
<normalizedToken id="EDE794DB26FC8E39D1601BDCBF38C83F" originalValue="“Guatemala,”">&quot;Guatemala,&quot;</normalizedToken>
however Monte Aguacate is located in Costa Rica, Province Alajuela. In her thesis, 
<bibRefCitation id="535AE6D6ED13C6DE6A69075F5B8962A6" author="Reyes-Cornejo, M" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B83" refString="Reyes-Cornejo, M, 2015. Sistematica de Lycianthes seccion Synantheroides (Solanaceae). M.S. Tesis, Posgrado en Ciencias Biologicas, Instituto de Biologia, Sistematica, Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico." title="Sistematica de Lycianthes seccion Synantheroides (Solanaceae). M. S. Tesis, Posgrado en Ciencias Biologicas, Instituto de Biologia, Sistematica, Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico." year="2015">Reyes Cornejo (2015)</bibRefCitation>
cited one specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="234DEF9DDED91953E81175D822D49E29" genus="L." lsidName="L. synanthera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="synanthera">
<emphasis id="78C098F02AC3521ED958CF7CD036DF47" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. synanthera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Guatemala, 
<emphasis id="CA0AA068C7FF811BCE24B426BAFD30B4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Steyermark 41657</emphasis>
(US), which is available as an online image, and this specimen is not 
<taxonomicName id="1898ACA2FB0D5DADFDE5F02A12CCF76E" genus="L." lsidName="L. synanthera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="synanthera">
<emphasis id="CF7FFBC164BB487CE6C0E3F9165FF5D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. synanthera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; it likely is 
<taxonomicName id="60EB131B0C810D43B872A3C9C2142204" authorityName="A.T.Hunziker" authorityYear="1977" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cuatresia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cuatresia" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CB7247187A37EDC1DECB138F2FFCD927" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cuatresia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All the Guatemalan specimens at herbarium MEXU that were previously identified as 
<taxonomicName id="5CAD99B0BA3E2F2CF852F9B67C671C93" genus="L." lsidName="L. synanthera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="synanthera">
<emphasis id="A985F4AB803F408AFE7B525C558666EE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. synanthera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been reidentified by the first author as 
<taxonomicName id="BF54194A9DC7248E3475127163227756" genus="L." lsidName="L. nitida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis id="4A607B3A5441F754164D00118703477C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="67485D6E337DC6E5660663DDEEBFC6E1" genus="L." lsidName="L. heteroclita" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="heteroclita">
<emphasis id="27501CA287FD519B04DF96AB9CBA3780" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. heteroclita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or 
<taxonomicName id="D639F47BF46438BA0F4C0262022A3B60" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Witheringia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Witheringia" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A4C91A93524DD71088B8BE3CFE7E3FBD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Witheringia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0CFDC0E2E3A178907EC9F98A01458ABC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
In his protologue for 
<taxonomicName id="86C6D9B83586E788A4B495E7FAF7ED3D" authorityName="Sendtn" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum synantherum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="synantherum">
<emphasis id="A86F008D37EAD6A0AD66C9F250F912FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum synantherum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="D7EE42AB56DDBE9ADDF33204CDBB864F" author="Sendtner, O" journalOrPublisher="Flora" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="193 - 195" refId="B94" refString="Sendtner, O, 1846. Beschreibung einer neuen Gattung der Familie der Solanaceen, so wie von zwei neuen etwas abweichenden Arten der Gattung Solanum. Flora 29 (13): 193 - 195" title="Beschreibung einer neuen Gattung der Familie der Solanaceen, so wie von zwei neuen etwas abweichenden Arten der Gattung Solanum." volume="29" year="1846">Sendtner (1846)</bibRefCitation>
just cited the one collection of Friedrichsthal (
<emphasis id="6C955C69B69D0618B491600240A35BA2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Friedrichsthal 1292</emphasis>
) with no specific herbarium cited. We located duplicates of this collection (syntypes) at both W and F: W [acc. # 0003083, acc. # 0003081, acc. # 0003082] and F [F0073153F, acc. # 871594]. We selected one of the specimens at W (acc. # 0003083) as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
